The '''RCA Type 77-DX microphone''' is a poly-directional [[ribbon microphone]] once made by the RCA Corporation.  Its design has inspired the stereotypical microphone icon.  
The directionality of the microphone is switch-selectable to either omnidirectional, unidirectional, or figure-8 (bidirectional).  

